def: A curve invented by Diocles, for the purpose of solving twocelebrated problems of the higher geometry; viz., to trisect a planeangle, and to construct two geometrical means between two givenstraight lines.
Very great; huge; vast; also, monstrous in character; inhuman;atrocious; fierce. [Obs.] "So immane a man." Chapman.-- Im*mane"ly, adv. [Obs.]
One who plays on a lute.
A genus of composite plants, with shining, commonly white oryellow, or sometimes reddish, radiated involucres, which are oftencalled "everlasting flowers."
A standing without moving forward or backward; a stop; a stateor rest.
One skilled in, or given to, microscopy.
One who inquires or examines; questioner; investigator. Locke.Expert inquirers after truth. Cowper.
A special substance contained in tuberculin, supposed to be theactive agent of the latter freed from various impurities.
